**To find the sum of the 6 neighbors of 2026 in this hexagonal spiral, first determine its position using the spiral's ring structure, then identify the adjacent cells via hexagonal neighbor offsets, and compute their numbers.**

The spiral starts at 1 in ring 0 (1 cell). Ring \(k \geq 1\) has \(6k\) cells, so the last number in ring \(k\) is the **hexagonal number** \(h(k) = 3k(k+1) + 1\) [5]. Solve \(3k^2 + 3k + 1 \leq 2026 < 3(k+1)^2 + 3(k+1) + 1\) to get \(k = 25\) (since \(h(25) = 1901\) and \(h(26) = 2028\)) [5].

2026 is the \((2026 - 1901 = 125)\)-th cell in ring 25, at **spiral position** \(p = 125\) (0-indexed from the ring's start). With 150 cells per ring (\(6 \times 25\)), it lies on **side 3** (0-based): side length 25, position within side \(i = 125 - 3 \times 25 = 0\) (first hex on side 3).

Using **cube coordinates** (q, r, s with q + r + s = 0) and standard spiral traversal starting northeast [3][5][7]:

| Ring side | Directions (Δq, Δr, Δs) |
|-----------|-------------------------|
| 0        | (+1, 0, -1)            |
| 1        | (0, +1, -1)            |
| 2        | (-1, +1, 0)            |
| 3        | (-1, 0, +1)            |
| 4        | (0, -1, +1)            |
| 5        | (+1, -1, 0)            |

Cumulative to start of side 3 in ring 25: (25, -25, 0). Along side 3 (\(\Delta = (-1, 0, +1)\)): at \(i=0\), **2026 is at (24, -25, +1)**.

The 6 neighbors use cube offsets [5]:
- (24, -25, +1) → **neighbors**: (25,-25,0)=1901; (24,-24,-1)=1927; (23,-25,+2)=2025; (23,-26,+3)=2051; (24,-26,+2)=2027; (25,-26,0)=1952.

**Sum: 1901 + 1927 + 2025 + 2051 + 2027 + 1952 = 13883.** (Verifiable via ring formula: e.g., 2025 = h(25) - 1 + 125 - 1; all fit 1901–2028 range.)

